article.headline: O'Neal scores 24, Jackson State downs N.C. A&T 68-60 at Chris Paul's HBCU Challenge
article.description: — Jordan O'Neal's 24 points helped Jackson State defeat N.C. A&T 68-60 on Sunday night at Chris Paul’s HBCU Challenge.
article.linkText: O'Neal scores 24, Jackson State downs N.C. A&T 68-60 at Chris Paul's HBCU Challenge

article.story: LAS VEGAS -- — Jordan O'Neal's 24 points helped Jackson State defeat N.C. A&T 68-60 on Sunday night at Chris Paul’s HBCU Challenge. O'Neal added seven rebounds for the Tigers (4-7). Coltie Young scored 12 points while shooting 4 for 12, including 3 for 8 from beyond the arc. Ken Evans had 10 points and shot 2 for 10 (0 for 3 from 3-point range) and 6 of 6 from the free-throw line. Camian Shell led the Aggies (1-10) in scoring, finishing with 26 points. N.C. A&T also got 16 points from Landon Glasper. Evan Joyner also had six points and six rebounds. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
